-- Indorama Ventures to Build Solar-Energy Project in Thailand, Post Reports
-- B y   B a l d a v e   S i n g h
-- 2010-11-08T02:17:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/indorama-ventures-to-build-solar-energy-project-in-thailand-post-reports.html
Indorama Ventures Pcl , Thailand’s
biggest producer of chemicals used in plastic bottles and
polyester, will set up a solar project at Lop Buri next year,
the Bangkok Post reported, citing a company executive it didn’t
identify.  The 2-megawatt plant will cost 275 million baht ($9.3
million) and will be located at the company’s chemicals plant,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
